@startuml agent-routing
title Agent Routing And Execution Sequence

autonumber
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Monospace
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

actor "Slack User" as slack_user
participant "Slack" as slack
participant "Slack Conversations API" as slack_api

box "Google Cloud Project"
  participant "Slack Events Endpoint\nPOST /slack/events" as slack_events_endpoint
  participant "Mention Handler" as mention_handler
  participant "Message Handler" as message_handler
  participant "Agent Routing" as agent_routing
  participant "Agent Selector" as agent_selector
  participant "Selected Agent" as selected_agent
  database "PostgreSQL\nslack_threads" as slack_threads
  participant "Vertex AI" as vertex_ai
end box

slack_user -> slack : Post a message in a channel or thread
alt Explicit agent invocation by mention
  slack -> slack_events_endpoint : app_mention event
  slack_events_endpoint -> mention_handler : Pass event payload
  mention_handler -> agent_routing : Build invocation\n(team, channel, thread, user text)
  agent_routing -> slack_threads : Read thread setting\n(agent_id)
  alt Agent already selected on the thread
    slack_threads --> agent_routing : Existing agent_id
  else Agent not selected on the thread
    slack_threads --> agent_routing : No agent_id
    agent_routing -> agent_selector : Select agent from user request\nand available agent candidates
    agent_selector -> vertex_ai : Reason over the request
    vertex_ai --> agent_selector : Recommended agent_id
    agent_selector --> agent_routing : Selected agent_id
    agent_routing -> slack_threads : Persist selected agent_id\nas thread setting
  end
else Follow-up message in an active agent thread
  slack -> slack_events_endpoint : message event
  slack_events_endpoint -> message_handler : Pass event payload
  message_handler -> slack_threads : Read thread state\n(agent_id, status)
  alt Thread has an active agent conversation
    slack_threads --> message_handler : Existing agent_id and active status
    message_handler -> agent_routing : Continue with thread agent\nwithout mention
  else No active agent conversation
    slack_threads --> message_handler : No active thread agent
    message_handler --> slack : No response
  end
end

agent_routing -> slack_api : Fetch full thread history\nvia Slack API (conversations.replies)
slack_api --> agent_routing : All thread messages\n(user posts + bot posts)
agent_routing -> selected_agent : Execute with selected agent_id\nand full thread messages
selected_agent -> vertex_ai : Generate reply from full thread context
vertex_ai --> selected_agent : Response content
selected_agent --> agent_routing : Agent output
agent_routing -> slack : Post reply to the thread
slack --> slack_user : Show agent response

note right of selected_agent
Basic behavior:
the agent reads all posts in the thread,
including user posts and bot posts,
and generates the output from that full context.
end note

note over agent_routing, slack_threads
Assumption for this diagram:
if selector fallback chooses an agent, the result is stored on the thread
so later mentions in the same thread reuse that agent directly.
end note

note over message_handler
Recommended guard conditions for message events:
- react only to user-authored messages
- ignore bot, edit, and delete related subtypes
- limit auto-replies to threads with an active agent conversation
end note

note over slack_api, selected_agent
Context collection rule:
retrieve the full thread from Slack API,
including both user messages and bot messages,
before running the selected agent.
end note

@enduml
